features.additionalInfo: If you want to withdraw your Business Investment Account before it matures you'll need to give us 31 days' notice. You may incur a prepayment adjustment and administration fee.

constraints.additionalInfo: There is no maximum limit (subject to acceptance by the Bank).

eligibility.additionalInfo: To be eligible you need to have a valid ABN, ACN, or an association created and operating in Australia. Further Eligibility depends on your specific organisation structure.

fees.name: Prepayment administration fee and prepayment adjustment
fees.additionalInfo: If you need to withdraw money during the term, you may request withdrawal of all or part of your funds by giving the Bank 31 days' notice. A prepayment adjustment and administration fee may apply to withdrawals before maturity.

You can give us instructions at any time, once you decide what you want to do.
